{"text": "(1.6) specifies the value of the electric field for each value of the position vector r. The word “field” signifies how some distributed quantity (which could be a scalar or a vector) varies with position.", "fibs": ["value"]}
{"text": "The effect of the charge has been incorporated in the existence of the electric field.", "fibs": ["effect"]}
{"text": "We obtain the force F exerted by a charge Q on a charge q, as
