{"text": "We can choose any positive value of k. The choice of k determines the size of the unit of charge.", "fibs": ["value"]}
{"text": "In SI units, the value of k is about 9 × 109 .", "fibs": ["SI"]}
{"text": "The unit of charge that results from this choice is called a coulomb which we defined earlier in Section 1.4.", "fibs": ["unit"]}
{"text": "Putting this value of k in Eq.", "fibs": ["value"]}
